title: Bournemouth
summary: Bournemouth (/ˈbɔːrnməθ/ (listen)) is a coastal resort town on the south coast of England. At the 2011 census, the town had a population of 183,491. With Poole to the west and Christchurch in the east, Bournemouth is part of the South East Dorset conurbation, which has a population of 465,000.
